Okay, while some shade might be thrown at the amount of awoo ladies in /hmofa/, it is still something people want. Don't worry too much about the species you choose.
Also two things:
1) Writing is both a hobby AND a skill. You have to put time in to git gud. What it is not, however, is a talent. Even the people who are 'natural' writers were probably gigantic book snorting nerds well versed in how one can use the English language long before they picked up the pen/opened up Wordpad. Tough to Love is the first thing I ever creatively wrote. Want to know why it wasn't an absolute dumpster fire despite being my first project? Because I worked for a year and a half as a college tutor proof reading and correcting papers, and took English classes for fun. That's not even counting the library I practically lived in. Technically my feet were already wet. If you're coming in new to the game, of course you're going to see other amateurs who have been putting in time and go "aw man I can't do that shit."

2) When it comes to creativity, post-modernism has you beat. Everything that could be created already has in some way, shape, or form, and all that jazz. So fuck it. So long as you're not recreating fucking Star Wars or some shit play by play, write that space opera with furries. People are going to bitch about lacking creativity, but I'll be honest sitting down and just brainstorming until you have a completely original idea before doing anything is just wasted time when you could have settled for a 60% original idea and used the rest of that time to catch up with your writing peers in word count and writing time. Save that kind of A1 effort for the serious publishers, not a Babylonian bird watching amphitheater on the internet.
